Text.string: Hey, Vaughn? I'm looking at a head in a jar. You know this person?
Vaughn, do you know whose head is in this jar?
Vaughn, do you know this decapitated bandit?
You got any friends missin' a head, Vaughn? Mighta found something.
Ah, no way! That's my deputy warchief Vic! She's my best bronette! Grab that head!
Oh, bee-tee-dubs—when they uploaded her, it probably fragmented her recent memories. You're gonna have to try to find them, so you can remind her who she is when she wakes up!

Memory fragment one.||What up, me? Our idiot-in-chief Vaughn finally made one good decision and made me the new Deputy Warchief of the Sun Smashers! He took his slappin' time replacing deputy Headcheese after he belly-flopped into a frickin' acid pit. Man, that dude knew how to party. Vaughn's all right, I guess, but he's no Headcheese.

Memory fragment two.||Yo, me, check this out. We found this crazy alien thing in the desert today. Brought it back to camp thinkin' we could sell it to the Children of the Vault. Those idiots are always buying crazy alien stuff like that! We're gonna be slappin' rich!

Memory fragment three.||Get this, me. So I showed Vaughn the crazy alien thing and he got super weird! Told me to hide it. Ughh, the whole clan could eat varkid caviar for months if we sold it to the COV! Now I look like the asshole 'cause I have to tell the clan we're not selling it. Slappin' idiot-in-chief! He doesn't know what's good for the clan.

Memory fragment four.||It's go time, me. This Mouthpiece idiot wants that alien thing and Vaughn won't sell it! We must be the last clan on Pandora that hasn't joined up with the COV. The Sun Smashers need new leadership. You know who I'm talking about, me. It's me.
Did you get all the memories? God, I can't wait to hear 'em myself! Y'know, Vic and I are TIGHT, always so supportive! Go get my best bronette out of that simulation!
Hey! Vic! I'm here to get you out!
Vic, this isn't real. Come with me!
Human, I can free you from this mind-prison.
Come on, time to break you out.
Hnnng. No! Can't leave! He'll twist my arms off again! It hurts so bad, but then they grow back! I don't understand! It's happened like fifty times already!
Hands off my captive!
You... you killed him, but... What the hell is happening? I don't slappin' understand!

They must have been interrogating her in VR! Y'know, we used that same tech back in Hyperion when we caught a corporate spy, or when someone's broccoli salad got stolen from the break room and I didn't have time to make more! Anyway, Vic's trapped in a virtual torture chamber, you gotta go in and get her out!
Oh, yeah. I'm a digital projection inside your own severed head. Don't worry about it.
You're in an impossible place where time is wrong and you can't die.
You are experiencing both existence and non-existence simultaneously. Do not think about it.
You don't remember? We tried to stage an elaborate surprise party and it's all gone horribly wrong.
This is slappin' weird. I'm freakin' out! You gotta get me out of here!
Ngh. What a slappin' nightmare! Thanks for getting me out of there!
Vic! You're—you're alive!
He's talking to me! Hey, Vaughn. Look, I'm a slappin' idiot. The COV are MESSED UP. We tried joining them and all they did was murder and torture us! In that order!

I'm afraid I'm gonna have to be pretty brutal with you right now, Vic. I'm gonna need you to gimme a hundred apology pushups! When you're done, come join me. We got a new clan now! Go Crimson Raiders.
Crimson Raiders? Yeah, I can dig it.
Oh, hey. You saved my slappin' life. Here, I nabbed this crazy gun while we were in that never-ending digital hell-prison. You can have it. It's all yours.
You all need to be around the VR console to jack in together! Jacking in is always better with a group! (beat) You heard me.
You want me to go... into the head.
Like... inside. Like inside the head.
Exciting. I have never hunted in a head before.
Yeah-yeah-yeah, I'm sold! Jack me in. Load me up! I'm goin' in that head!
You all have to be there, bro!
I mean, technically.
Hey, as long as you're doin' the pushups.
Well, this is awkward.
Oh come on, I mean, I always wanted more “me time”, right? This is perfect! I get to hang with my favorite person!
I mean, are you me? Or am I you?
Woah.
Mind. Blown. Right? And I'm, like, eighty percent mind right now.
Do I need to, like... feed you or whatever?
I think whatever this stuff I'm floating in is keeping me going. I don't even have a digestive system anymore! BUT, I do have tastebuds! How 'bout you just drip some gravy in here for me?
There should be a VR console by the gate to the HBC. Just hook her head up and your ECHO device will digistruct you right into the VR construct.
You're livin' the dream!
Maybe getting connected to a torture device for a simulated eternity of unspeakable horrors wasn't such a bad deal after all!
Yeah, high five!
Dude. Not cool.
Heh-heh.||—Oh, right. Sorry.
I'd go in there myself, but, uh... VR stuff totally squicks me out. No one's gonna take my body apart molecule by molecule without a fight! I'm an analog man!

I gotta say, I'm surprised the COV are using VR tech, but... y'know, then again it's pretty cheap these days! I mean, people make entire worlds in there and just live in 'em! It's weird, though, y'know? Most people just revisit worlds that were made like... seven years ago?
Vic's plugged in? Awesome. Now get in that digital torture room and save her, bro!
You're in the simulation, bro! Vic's somewhere in there. You gotta find her and break her out!
Take her to the exit console inside the construct! That'll rebuild her body in the meatspace! I need my best bronette in one meaty piece!
